@database "Table Font Guide"
@author "Heiko Schr—der"
@$VER: 3.0 (Release 3)
@wordwrap

@node Main "Table Font V1.0"
                               @{" < Table of contents " link "Macro-Package.guide/Main"}

         !!! This macro only works with £Final Writer 5¨ !!!

@{fg shine}Benifits:@{fg text}
   Manipulating tables in FinalWriter is very easy to get wrong and is
   therefore very uncomfortable.
   With this you can alter the Font, alignment and Font size very simply.

@{fg shine}Requirements:@{fg text}
   £Final Writer 5¨ or latter
   A Table ;-)

@{fg shine}Using the @{"macro" system "Sys:Utilities/Multiview TabFont.iff"}:@{fg text}

   @{fg fill}F@{fg text}ont:
      Here you can select a new font.
      If you do no want to set a font, leave this Field empty.

   @{fg fill}S@{fg text}ize:
      Here you can select a new font size.
      If you do not want to set a font size, leave this Field empty.

   @{fg fill}T@{fg text}ext Alignment:
      You can select the alignment of the text.
      You use the standard settings (left, central, right, flushed).
      With "---" the alignment is ignored.

                     - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - 

   @{fg fill}A@{fg text}pply
      This begins the alterations, You must select the first cell, by
      activating it. Then you select the last cell, by activating it.
      The alterations will then commence.

   @{fg fill}C@{fg text}ancel
   @{fg fill}ESC@{fg text} or closing the window
      Terminates the macro.
@endnode
